<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[828,1469,1722,1956]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sefrji &amp; Michoud &amp; Marasco &amp; Merlino &amp; Daffonchio" authorityYear="2021" box="[828,982,1764,1787]" class="Cytophagia" family="Flammeovirgaceae" genus="Mangrovivirga" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Cytophagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bacteroidetes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,982,1764,1787]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Mangrovivirga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Man.gro.vi.vir′ ga. N.L. neut. n. 
<emphasis box="[1339,1466,1764,1787]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">mangrovum</emphasis>
a mangrove; L. fem. n. 
<emphasis box="[1071,1124,1795,1818]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">virga</emphasis>
rod; N.L. fem. n. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sefrji &amp; Michoud &amp; Marasco &amp; Merlino &amp; Daffonchio" authorityYear="2021" box="[1312,1466,1795,1818]" class="Cytophagia" family="Flammeovirgaceae" genus="Mangrovivirga" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Cytophagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bacteroidetes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1312,1466,1795,1818]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Mangrovivirga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a mangrove rod, referring to the isolation of a rod-shaped bacterium from the mangrove environment).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[828,1469,1722,1956]" lastBlockId="8.[121,762,183,391]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Cells of the species are strictly aerobic, Gram-stain-negative, long-rod-shaped, moderately halophilic, non-spore-forming, non-motile, catalase-positive and oxidase-negative. The major respiratory quinone is MK7 and the major polar lipids are phosphatidylethanolamine, two unknown phospholipids and two unknown lipids. The major cellular fatty acids (&gt;5%) are iso-C 
<subScript attach="left" box="[217,243,321,336]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">15:0</subScript>
, C 
<subScript attach="both" box="[274,301,321,336]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">16:1</subScript>
<emphasis box="[303,322,306,329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">ω</emphasis>
5 
<emphasis box="[334,344,306,329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">c</emphasis>
, iso-C 
<subScript attach="left" box="[414,441,322,336]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">17:0</subScript>
and iso-C 
<subScript attach="left" box="[552,578,322,336]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">17:0</subScript>
3-OH. The G+C content of the genomic DNA is 63.1mol%. The 
<typeStatus box="[614,659,336,360]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sefrji &amp; Michoud &amp; Marasco &amp; Merlino &amp; Daffonchio" authorityYear="2021" box="[121,355,367,391]" class="Cytophagia" family="Flammeovirgaceae" genus="Mangrovivirga" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Cytophagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacteroidetes" rank="species" species="cuniculi">
<emphasis box="[121,355,367,391]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mangrovivirga cuniculi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
